What is CalFresh?
CalFresh, also known as
Supplemental Nutrition Assistance
 Program (SNAP)
throughout the United States, is a program that
 provides low income households with monthly benefits to buy food.
 CalFresh benefits can help supplement the food budget of a household
 allowing them to buy more nutritious foods. Eligibility to CalFresh
 and the amount of benefits a household may receive depends on the
 household's size, income, and expenses.
CalFresh benefits are provided on an Electronic Benefit Transfer
 (EBT) card and can be used to buy food at participating grocery
 stores, online stores, and farmers markets.

In need of food right away?
Apply for CalFresh
and you may
 be eligible to receive benefits in as few as 3 days. You can also get
 food by visiting
San Diego Food Bank
,
Feeding San Diego
, or
 calling
211 San Diego
.
Learn how SUN Bucks can help you buy food for your children
SUN
 Bucks
, also known as Summer EBT, is a new program to help families
 buy food for their school-aged children while on summer break. You do
 not need to apply for SUN Bucks if your household is receiving
 CalFresh.  Each school-aged child in your household will receive a SUN
 Bucks EBT card loaded with $120 in benefits to purchase food. Children
 who get SUN Bucks can still participate in other summer meals programs.
